{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c1025fe3-911e-4335-b0c2-700b9be0f2b6","content":"The template is **not quite ready** to publish. Here are the issues:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation and editor support (e.g., `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`)\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- `preferNameDirectory` — should typically be `true` for project templates\n- `description` — without this, NuGet listing will lack a summary\n- `groupIdentity` — needed if you plan multiple language/framework variants\n\n**Other concerns:**\n- `\"defaultValue\": \"net9.0\"` — .NET 9 is STS (end-of-support May 2026). Consider whether `net8.0` (LTS) is a safer default.\n- No `precedence` set, which matters if users install multiple versions side-by-side.\n\n**Minimum fix to be publish-ready:** add a `description` field — NuGet strongly expects it for discoverability. The rest are best-practice but not blockers.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2c2c1fd2-61ba-4009-a95b-1132c9de0c53","outputTokens":234,"requestId":"1C15:3932DE:AC932C3:BB44983:69FD34E7"},"id":"44cd3c7d-2863-4632-81f4-978d7a7915ea","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:57:19.131Z","parentId":"56d58db0-cfb1-4b6b-ad85-3903942a58d5"}
